      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Amazing",
          "reviewText": "I have bought 2 of these. I receive many compliments on my complexion. This foundation is best for an avid makeup user. Great m for an intermediate to advanced makeup user. This is not the type of foundation that you could just smear on your face. You have to intentionally apply for the best results. I had wonderful results while using this foundation. I am absolutely obsessed and I love the way my face looks, and it\u2019s a long lasting. This type of foundation you have to blot on your entire face and not smear on. Having the knowledge of applying application is a must for this for the best results. Compatibility, lightweight while having great coverage. Application is great with knowledge. Non fragrant.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2026",
          "customer": "Maneadvocate",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHS4NXOF74VJHV2LRYNM4IHOVQDQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "size": "0.63 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)",
            "color": "24W Soft Beige"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "One person found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "CONCEAled my burn mark like magic!",
          "reviewText": "EDIT: The shade in this video is the second shade I bought natural beige 29N and I think this is a better color for me! It CONCEALED MY burn mark like magic as you can see! \ud83c\udf38 My Experience with the TIRTIR Mask Fit AI Filter Cushion Foundation (24W Soft Beige). This is the first shade I bought and is slightly lighter for me in the summer. I\u2019ve been using the TIRTIR Mask Fit AI Filter Cushion Foundation in 24W Soft Beige for a little while now, and honestly, I was really curious if it would live up to all the hype. Here\u2019s how it worked for me: \u2728 First Impressions When I first opened the compact, I loved how sleek and sturdy it felt. The puff is soft and makes application so easy \u2014 just a few taps and it blended right into my skin. I don\u2019t like foundations that feel heavy, so I was pleasantly surprised at how lightweight this cushion is, even though it gives good coverage. \ud83d\udd8c\ufe0f Application & Finish On my skin, one thin layer was enough to even out redness and little blemishes, but when I had a breakout, I tapped on a second layer and it still looked natural (not cakey at all!). The finish is really pretty \u2014 it\u2019s semi-matte but still has a soft glow that makes my skin look healthy. I like that it doesn\u2019t give that flat \u201cmask\u201d look some foundations can. \u23f3 Wear Test The first time I wore it was on a busy workday, and I honestly forgot I had foundation on. It stayed smooth for about 8\u20139 hours without separating, even around my T-zone where I usually get shiny. By the end of the day, I did notice a little fading around my nose, but nothing major \u2014 a quick touch-up fixed it right away. I wouldn\u2019t say it\u2019s a true \u201c72-hour\u201d foundation like the brand claims (who really wears makeup that long anyway?), but it definitely lasts all day for me. \ud83d\udca7 Skin Type Notes My skin is on the combination side \u2014 oily in the T-zone, drier on my cheeks. This foundation works really well on my oily areas, but I did notice it clings a little if I don\u2019t moisturize my dry patches properly. When I prep my skin with a good moisturizer, it goes on flawlessly. \ud83c\udfa8 Shade Match The shade 24W Soft Beige works nicely for me with its warm undertone. That being said, I think the shade range is a bit limited \u2014 people with very deep or very fair tones might have a harder time finding a match. \ud83d\udcad Overall Thoughts What I really love is how comfortable it feels. I can wear it all day without feeling like my skin can\u2019t breathe. It\u2019s now my go-to when I want medium-to-full coverage that looks smooth and polished but still feels light. Would I recommend it? Yes, especially if you like cushion foundations and want something that lasts all day. Just make sure to prep your skin if you\u2019re on the drier side.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2025",
