        {
          "reviewTitle": "Good product, but not the right one for my skin",
          "reviewText": "I am really glad I tried this, and it\u2019s lovely that TirTir offers a mini size and many color options. I went with 15C Fair Porcelain, and it was a pretty good match. If you like the formula, coverage, and finish, keep searching for the right shade. I can\u2019t say I have noticed color changes/oxidation as some other reviewers have reported. Foundation is such a personal choice! I have tried several forms, so I figured I\u2019d better cross cushion foundation off my list. This was a good one to try. Like I said in the title, it\u2019s a good product. I don\u2019t think it\u2019s right for my skin and the way I prefer to wear makeup. I am 40 with combination skin, noticeable fine lines, and serious rosacea. I\u2019m most used to liquid foundations. It\u2019s my preference to apply foundation \u201cwhere needed\u201d to cover the reddest regions of my face, blending it into the parts of my face that aren\u2019t red, and avoiding that full-makeup look (which is lovely if that\u2019s what you want, it\u2019s just not my look). This particular foundation looks patchy if I just use it on the parts I want to cover. I feel like I have to commit to the entire face if I want it to look right, and then it doesn\u2019t look at all like my skin. So I feel much less natural with this foundation on. It\u2019s also very drying for my skin. Perhaps the biggest qualm: even with a quality primer, this foundation makes itself right at home in every little crevice on my face right away. The attached photo is from five minutes after application. Note the horizontal forehead lines. This becomes more obvious as the hours wear on. So no, it\u2019s not something I will buy again. If you\u2019re on the fence, try it in this adorable mini size. I read all the reviews with photos in which reviewers mentioned the shades they ordered, and I tried to make my color choice based on the lightest-toned folks I saw.",
